  "2026-06-04T16:47:14.795Z",codex-sdk-continuation,"Review follow-up evidence: addressed Gemini feedback on PR #110 by making close-many filter guards ignore null/empty programmatic filters, sorting close-many matched items by parent-depth descending so children close before parents under strict validation, adding null-safe status/date/id parsing, and using optional chaining for update-many rollback options. Focused verification passed: pnpm build; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/close-command.spec.ts tests/unit/list-command.spec.ts tests/unit/status-normalization.spec.ts tests/unit/update-many-command.spec.ts (105 tests)."
  "2026-06-04T16:49:55.169Z",codex-sdk-continuation,"Review follow-up verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed after Gemini fixes with 137 files / 2258 tests / 100% coverage; pnpm changelog:pm:check with pm-changelog@2026.6.4 still reports CHANGELOG.md unchanged (item_count 961)."
  "2026-06-04T17:10:19.884Z",codex-sdk-continuation,"Second review follow-up evidence: addressed new PR #110 review comments by translating MCP pm_run close-many flat filter options into the nested CLI shape, exposing list --ids in command registration, sanitizing inactive/null filters before bulk list evaluation, rejecting close-many rollback limit/offset, preserving child-before-parent strict close ordering with cached hierarchy depth, wrapping malformed checkpoint JSON in PmCliError, and clarifying help/completion text. Verification passed: pnpm build; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/close-command.spec.ts tests/unit/list-command.spec.ts tests/unit/update-many-command.spec.ts tests/unit/status-normalization.spec.ts tests/integration/mcp-dynamic-package-actions.spec.ts (5 files, 117 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (137 files, 2263 tests, 100% coverage); pnpm changelog:pm:check with pm-changelog 2026.6.4 unchanged at 961 closed items."
  "2026-06-04T17:33:24.356Z",codex-sdk-continuation,"Third review follow-up evidence: addressed new PR #110 findings by rejecting whitespace/comma-only bulk close filters, making close-many list options optional/null-safe, treating empty list date/id filters as omitted, making close-many warnings optional-safe, mapping MCP pm_run update-many flat options into nested list/update/control shapes, keeping update-many filter selectors out of update options, exposing list --ids in CLI and tool contracts, and applying/planning runtime fields registered for update_many by collecting update/update_many runtime values and counting them before runUpdate's no-op guard. Verification passed: pnpm build; focused test run (6 files, 125 tests); node dist/cli.js contracts --command list --flags-only --json confirmed --ids; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (137 files, 2269 tests, 100% coverage); pnpm changelog:pm:check with pm-changelog 2026.6.4 unchanged at 961 closed items."
  "2026-06-04T17:42:30.175Z",codex-sdk-continuation,"Fourth review follow-up evidence: fixed Gemini high-priority finding in close-many rollback conflict detection by converting programmatic numeric limit/offset values with String(...) before trimming, preventing TypeError crashes for MCP/API callers. Added regression coverage for numeric rollback limit/offset. Verification passed: pnpm build; focused test run (6 files, 126 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (137 files, 2270 tests, 100% coverage); pnpm changelog:pm:check with pm-changelog 2026.6.4 unchanged at 961 closed items."
  "2026-06-04T17:52:04.681Z",codex-sdk-continuation,"Review follow-up 5: post-push review window found fresh actionable issues on commit 550507d12e. Fixing MCP bulk option normalization for numeric filters/limits, structured update-many payloads, update-many alias normalization, and buildPlannedItemDiff undefined update safety before another verification/push/review cycle."
  "2026-06-04T17:57:29.084Z",codex-sdk-continuation,"Review follow-up 5 evidence: addressed latest PR #110 comments by preserving numeric MCP bulk filters/limits via scalar coercion, forwarding structured MCP update-many {list,update} payloads, normalizing flat update-many mutation aliases through normalizeUpdateOptions (including numeric estimate aliases), and making buildPlannedItemDiff safe for undefined update options. Verification passed: pnpm build; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/mcp-dynamic-package-actions.spec.ts tests/unit/update-many-command.spec.ts (2 files, 37 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (137 files, 2272 tests, 100% coverage); pnpm changelog:pm:check with pm-changelog 2026.6.4 unchanged at 961 closed items."
  "2026-06-04T18:03:54.706Z",codex-sdk-continuation,"Review follow-up 6: latest Gemini review on commit 261538e8 found nested MCP list payloads were cast directly instead of normalized. Fixing normalizeListOptions numeric coercion for known list fields, routing nested MCP update-many/close-many list payloads through it, and adding regressions before another verification/push/review wait."
  "2026-06-04T18:07:19.118Z",codex-sdk-continuation,"Review follow-up 6 evidence: addressed latest Gemini nested MCP list feedback by importing normalizeListOptions in the MCP adapter, routing nested update-many and close-many list payloads through it, and extending normalizeListOptions to stringify numeric known list scalar aliases such as priority/limit/offset. Added nested numeric list regressions for MCP update-many and close-many. Verification passed: pnpm build; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/mcp-dynamic-package-actions.spec.ts tests/unit/update-many-command.spec.ts (2 files, 37 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (137 files, 2272 tests, 100% coverage); pnpm changelog:pm:check with pm-changelog 2026.6.4 unchanged at 961 closed items."
  "2026-06-04T18:28:35.556Z",codex-sdk-continuation,"Review follow-up 7: final post-wait sweep found new Codex comments on commit 1892077f. Fixing mixed nested-list/flat-update MCP update-many payloads, scalar-to-array normalization for nested update repeatables, nested list.status scoping guards for close-many and update-many rollback, and runtime-field update/update_many command scoping before another verification/push/review wait."
  "2026-06-04T18:35:53.362Z",codex-sdk-continuation,"Review follow-up 7 evidence: addressed latest Codex findings by preserving flat mutation fields when MCP update-many uses nested list without nested update, promoting scalar nested update-many repeatables through normalizeOptionsArrays, including nested list.status in close-many scope checks and update-many rollback filter conflicts, and making runtime field collection command-aware so update_many-only fields are not writable by regular update while still applying through update-many. Verification passed: pnpm build; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/mcp-dynamic-package-actions.spec.ts tests/unit/update-many-command.spec.ts tests/unit/close-command.spec.ts tests/unit/update-command.spec.ts (4 files, 152 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (137 files, 2277 tests, 100% coverage); pnpm changelog:pm:check with pm-changelog 2026.6.4 unchanged at 961 closed items."
  "2026-06-04T18:57:06.913Z",codex-sdk-continuation,"Review follow-up 8: post-wait sweep found new Gemini/Codex comments on commit acce8b8c. Fixing defensive non-string handling for status/date/id/reason/runtime command inputs, warning length idiom, update-many runtime field scope to update_many-only, and top-level MCP pm_run close-many reason forwarding before another verification/push/review wait."
  "2026-06-04T19:01:54.610Z",codex-sdk-continuation,"Review follow-up 8 evidence: addressed latest Gemini/Codex findings by defensively handling non-string status filters, list date/id filters, close-many reasons, and nullable runtime command scopes; using a safer close-many warnings length check; restricting update-many runtime fields to update_many-only; and forwarding top-level MCP pm_run close-many reason into runner options. Verification passed: pnpm build; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/mcp-dynamic-package-actions.spec.ts tests/unit/update-many-command.spec.ts tests/unit/close-command.spec.ts tests/unit/list-command.spec.ts tests/unit/status-normalization.spec.ts (5 files, 133 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (137 files, 2279 tests, 100% coverage); pnpm changelog:pm:check with pm-changelog 2026.6.4 unchanged at 961 closed items."
  "2026-06-04T19:23:17.867Z",codex-sdk-continuation,"Review follow-up 9: final sweep found new comments on commit 6c6d4b9a. Fixing blank ids rejection for explicit --ids, close-many active-child dry-run warnings when children are also in the batch, top-level MCP pm_run close-many force forwarding, update-many runtime-field contract discovery for update_many-only fields, and hierarchyDepth caching polish before another verification/push/review wait."
  "2026-06-04T19:31:31.024Z",codex-sdk-continuation,"Review follow-up 9 evidence: addressed latest current-commit comments by rejecting explicit blank --ids before list/update-many/close-many bulk evaluation, suppressing close-many active_child_ids warnings for children also planned in the same batch, forwarding top-level MCP pm_run close-many force, advertising update_many runtime fields in update-many contracts, and caching intermediate hierarchyDepth values. Verification passed: pnpm build; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/list-command.spec.ts tests/unit/close-command.spec.ts tests/unit/update-many-command.spec.ts tests/unit/contracts-command.spec.ts tests/integration/mcp-dynamic-package-actions.spec.ts (5 files, 114 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (137 files, 2281 tests, 100% coverage); pnpm changelog:pm:check with pm-changelog 2026.6.4 unchanged at 961 closed items."
